    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Activity 1.1.1: Support local government with medical equipment and preventive gears in coordination with DCCMCActivity 1.1.2: Risk messaging, awareness campaigns to raise awareness on COVID-19 and address the myths about COVID vaccination through different media platforms. (Govt approved messages)Activity 1.2.1: Support government with vaccination program and the vaccination centres allocated by the government with focus on improving health facilities.Activity 1.2.2: Rehabilitation/ establishment of handwashing stations, filtration units, waste management, Menstrual Health Management (MHM) at Schools, health facilities, isolation centres along with dissemination of relevant preventive messaging.Activity 2.1.1: Most vulnerable households (especially girls, women and children with disability and children at risk) provided with value vouchers (NPR 13500 per household for 2 months) to support with their livelihood.Activity 2.2.1: Disseminate protection related awareness messages through public service announcement and social behavioral change communication materials in various platforms.Activity 3.1.1: In coordination with schools, provide relevant trainings to teachers on alternative mode of education, remote teaching and learning, and support schools to be functional.Activity 3.2.1: Children provided with self-learning materials, alternative remedial classes and create an enabling learning environment at home and at school once it reopens, including minor school repairs."
      },
      "ne": null
    },
